# Cursor Rules — BikeHaus Freiburg

## Project

BikeHaus Freiburg — Bicycle shop inventory & sales management system.
Full-stack: .NET 9 backend + Angular 17 frontend + SQLite database.

## Architecture (Clean Architecture)

- `BikeHaus.Domain` → Entities, Enums, Repository interfaces (no dependencies)
- `BikeHaus.Application` → DTOs, Service interfaces, Service implementations
- `BikeHaus.Infrastructure` → EF Core DbContext, Repositories, Auth/PDF/File services
- `BikeHaus.API` → Controllers, Program.cs (DI, middleware)
- `BikeHaus.Client` → Angular SPA

## Backend Rules

- Entity properties in German: Marke, Modell, Preis, Vorname, Nachname
- .NET 9 / net9.0 / EF Core 8 + SQLite
- File-scoped namespaces: `namespace X;`
- Repository + Service pattern
- DI registrations in `BikeHaus.Infrastructure/DependencyInjection.cs`
- Controller routes: `api/[controller]`
- Decimal fields: `decimal(18,2)`
- JSON: camelCase + JsonStringEnumConverter
- Nullable enabled project-wide
- Async methods with `Async` suffix

## Frontend Rules

- Angular 17 standalone components (NO NgModule)
- Signal-based state: `signal()`, `computed()`
- Functional guards & interceptors
- Models in `src/app/models/models.ts` (central file)
- Service per module: `bicycle.service.ts`, `sale.service.ts`
- `TranslationService` for DE/TR/EN
- `ThemeService` for dark/light mode
- PascalCase for interfaces/enums, camelCase for properties

## Key Entities

Bicycle, Customer, Purchase, Sale, SaleAccessory, Reservation, Return,
Expense, Document, Signature, AccessoryCatalog, ShopSettings, User

## Enums

BikeStatus(Available/Sold/Reserved), BikeCondition(Neu/Gebraucht),
PaymentMethod(Bar/PayPal/Karte), ReservationStatus(Active/Converted/Expired/Cancelled),
ReturnReason(Defekt/NichtWieErwartet/Garantie/Sonstiges),
DocumentType(Screenshot/PDF/Image/Kaufbeleg/Verkaufsbeleg/Rechnung),
SignatureType(Seller/Buyer/ShopOwner)

## New Feature Checklist

Backend: Entity → Enum → Repo Interface → DTOs → Service Interface → Service Impl → Repo Impl → DbContext → DI → Controller → Migration
Frontend: Model (models.ts) → Service → Page Component → Route (app.routes.ts) → Sidebar (app.component.ts)
